article.headline: Wright St. 60, Youngstown St. 59
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio -- Todd Brown hit two go-ahead free throws with 33 seconds left to help Wright State rally for a 60-59 victory over Youngstown State on Saturday night. Vytas Sulskis hit a 3-pointer with 2:04 left to break a 56-56 tie and put Youngstown State (4-9, 1-3 Horizon League) ahead. John David Gardner made a jumper for Wright State (8-7, 2-2) with 53 seconds left to cut the Penguins' lead to a point. Brown, who scored joined teammates Cory Cooperwood and Cooper Land with 11 points each, then hit his two foul shots. DeAndre Mays, who led Youngstown State with 15 points, missed a 3-pointer with 15 seconds left, but it was rebounded by a teammate. After a timeout, he missed again with 5 seconds remaining -- with Brown grabbing the rebounding. Jack Liles added 12 points and Sirlester Martin 10 for the Penguins, who led 33-20 at the half.
